# Guide Templates

Use these templates selectively. Match the user's deliverable rather than filling every section by default.

## Full Educational Guide

```markdown
# [Official Site Name]

## Quick Profile
- Location:
- UNESCO type:
- Inscribed:
- Criteria:
- Why it matters:
- Best audience fit:

## Big Idea
[One teachable central idea that connects the site to history, culture, nature, preservation, or identity.]

## Site Overview
[Plain-language profile with the official name, setting, and defining features.]

## Historical, Cultural, Or Natural Context
[Chronological, cultural, ecological, geological, or architectural context. Keep it specific to the site.]

## Outstanding Universal Value
[Explain the UNESCO significance in accessible language, tied to official criteria.]

## Map Context
[Where the site is, what it connects to, why location matters, and any relevant landscape or route relationships.]

## Timeline
| Date/Period | Event | Why It Matters |
|---|---|---|

## Preservation And Stewardship
[Threats, conservation efforts, governance, local community roles, tourism pressure, climate concerns, or restoration debates.]

