## Museum Label

```markdown
**[Label Title]**  
[Date/period, place, culture/community, material/ecosystem if relevant]

[60 to 120 words. Lead with one interpretive idea. Explain why the site/object matters and what visitors should notice.]
```

For family labels, use 40 to 70 words and one question.

For scholarly exhibit panels, use 150 to 250 words, include context, and avoid overloaded chronology.

